-- Canadian Stocks Retreat as Raw Material Shares Slide
-- B y   L e s l i e   P i c k e r
-- 2013-02-20T15:40:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-20/canadian-stocks-retreat-as-raw-material-shares-slide.html
Canadian  stocks  fell after posting
the biggest gain in three months yesterday as home resale prices
slid for a fifth month and metal prices dropped.  Aurizon Mines Ltd . and China Gold International Resources
Corp Ltd. decreased at least 2.6 percent as gold futures fell to
a six-month low. Industrial Alliance Insurance & Financial
Services Inc. lost 4.5 percent after Canaccord Genuity Corp. cut
the insurer to hold from buy. Semafo Inc., which operates three
gold mines in West Africa, gained 2.5 percent as Goldman Sachs
Group Inc. recommended buying the shares.  The  Standard & Poor’s/TSX Composite Index  dropped 27.22
points, or 0.2 percent, to 12,782.99 at 10:38 a.m. in Toronto.
The S&P/TSX has risen 2.8 percent this year.  Canadian home resale prices fell for a fifth straight month
in January, the longest string of declines since the country’s
2009 recession, according to the Teranet-National Bank Composite
House Price Index. Government data in the U.S. showed builders
broke ground on the most single-family homes in more than four
years.  To contact the reporter on this story:
